# Modern Icons Across the Site

Use a single, modern icon library for all UI icons. Prefer **Lucide** or **Heroicons** (SVG) for consistency and accessibility.

## How to Add Icons

1. **Include the library once** (e.g. in a shared header or layout):
   - Lucide: `<script src="https://unpkg.com/lucide@latest"></script>` then `lucide.createIcons();`
   - Or inline SVG from [Lucide](https://lucide.dev) / [Heroicons](https://heroicons.com) copied into the page.

2. **Mark decorative icons** so screen readers skip them:
   ```html
   <i data-lucide="user" aria-hidden="true"></i>
   ```
   Or for inline SVG:
   ```html
   <svg aria-hidden="true" class="w-5 h-5" ...>...</svg>
   ```

3. **When the icon is the only label** (e.g. icon-only button), give it an accessible name:
   ```html
   <button type="submit" aria-label="כניסה">
     <i data-lucide="log-in" aria-hidden="true"></i>
   </button>
   ```

## Do Not

- Use emoji as the primary UI control (e.g. 🔑 for login). Emoji are OK for decorative or status only.
- Mix multiple icon sets on the same page.
- Omit `aria-hidden="true"` on purely decorative icons.

## Example (RTL-friendly)

```html
<span class="nav-item">
  <i data-lucide="package" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  <span>ניהול ציוד</span>
</span>
```
